---
/**
 * /magpie/pitch — 90-second overview.
 *
 * The "I have ninety seconds, sell me" page. One big idea on top,
 * four concrete things it does, three honest pieces about what it
 * isn't, one install CTA. Should read end-to-end in under two minutes.
 *
 * Sibling /magpie/tour is the 12-slide interactive version.
 * Sibling /magpie/guide is the long-form walkthrough.
 */

import BlockLayout from '../../layouts/BlockLayout.astro';
---

<BlockLayout
  channelCode="FD"
  blockType="NOTE"
  title="Magpie · 90-second overview"
  description="What Magpie is, in under two minutes."
  pageTitle="Magpie — 90 seconds"
>
  <article class="mgp-root">
    <header class="mgp-head">
      <p class="mgp-kicker">90 seconds · no fluff</p>
      <h1 class="mgp-title">Magpie is a clipboard that broadcasts.</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="mgp-block mgp-bold">
      <p>
        You're in Safari. You copy a Spotify link. Or a paragraph. Or a
        cast. Or a Zora URL. <strong>Magpie holds it.</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        Right-click the clipping in Magpie's menu-bar popover. Hit
        <em>Broadcast…</em> The composer opens. Eleven destinations are
        waiting. Each one shows a live preview — char count, thread
        warnings, embeds.
      </p>
      <p>
        Pick a preset (<em>Social · Web3 · Long-form · Mesh · Visual · All</em>).
        Hit <strong>Publish</strong>. It fans out to every destination
        in parallel. One compose, many homes.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mgp-block mgp-does">
      <h2>What it does</h2>
      <div class="mgp-does-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="mgp-does-h">Capture</p>
          <p>
            Everything you copy lands in a searchable local archive.
            URL clips auto-unfurl (title, OG image, host). Image clips
            keep bytes. File paths stay clickable.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="mgp-does-h">Broadcast</p>
          <p>
            Eleven destinations behind one protocol. Per-destination
            overrides tweak copy per platform. Image attachments with
            IPFS auto-staging. Threading where supported.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="mgp-does-h">Schedule</p>
          <p>
            Clock button → pick a time (or preset: +1 HR, TOMORROW 9A).
            Local scheduler fires while Magpie runs. Cloud scheduler
            on pointcast.xyz fires while your laptop sleeps.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="mgp-does-h">Measure</p>
          <p>
            Reach tab shows 30-day totals, per-destination success-rate
            lanes, 14-day histogram, block-type split. Activity feed
            drills into each outcome with permalinks + retries.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mgp-block mgp-honest">
      <h2>What it <em>isn't</em></h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Not a SaaS.</strong> Magpie runs on your Mac. Your
          clipboard never leaves the device unless you press push.
          Credentials live in Keychain.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Not a composer-first tool.</strong> You don't open
          Magpie to write. You open the apps you were already in and
          copy what caught your eye. Magpie is the relay.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Not a CRM, not a CMS, not a scheduler-only.</strong>
          It's one wedge — the step between capture and publish — done
          carefully across everywhere you already live.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mgp-block mgp-technical">
      <h2>Under the hood</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Native macOS SwiftUI — menu-bar app, no Electron</li>
        <li>SQLite-backed clipboard history, local-only</li>
        <li>Publisher protocol with per-adapter capabilities, auth, preview rendering</li>
        <li>Keychain-scoped credentials, namespaced per publisher</li>
        <li>Local HTTP peer node on 127.0.0.1:38473 — scriptable + agent-writable</li>
        <li>OAuth 2.0 PKCE via loopback callback (Twitter, LinkedIn)</li>
        <li>secp256k1 ECDSA + Schnorr + Tezos ed25519 for MINT + bitchat</li>
        <li>AES-GCM-256 encrypted credential envelopes for cloud scheduling</li>
        <li>Cloudflare Pages Functions + KV for the cloud scheduler</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mgp-block mgp-who">
      <h2>Who it's for</h2>
      <p>
        People who run <em>multiple homes</em> on the social + Web3 web
        and never want to write the same thing twice. Writers, artists,
        minters, broadcasters. Also: agent builders who want their
        clipboard to be an API the model can write through.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mgp-block mgp-cta">
      <a class="mgp-btn" href="https://github.com/Good-Feels/magpie/releases/latest" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        Download Magpie v1.0
      </a>
      <p class="mgp-cta-meta">macOS 13+ · free · open source</p>
      <nav class="mgp-nav">
        <a href="/magpie/tour">→ 12-slide tour</a>
        <a href="/magpie/guide">→ long-form guide</a>
        <a href="/magpie/faq">→ FAQ</a>
      </nav>
    </section>
  </article>
</BlockLayout>

<style>
  :root {
    --mg-paper: #EFE8D2;
    --mg-paper-tint: #E7DFC4;
    --mg-card: #FAF5E0;
    --mg-rule: #C8B98E;
    --mg-rule-soft: #E0D6B6;
    --mg-ink: #1E1C14;
    --mg-ink-soft: #5A544A;
    --mg-ink-mute: #8A8273;
    --mg-moss: #3E5940;
    --mg-clay: #AE6A38;
    --mg-bronze: #7E5A2A;
    --mg-display: Georgia, 'Iowan Old Style', serif;
    --mg-mono: ui-monospace, 'IBM Plex Mono', 'SF Mono', Menlo, monospace;
  }

  .mgp-root {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 40px 24px 80px;
    background: var(--mg-paper);
    color: var(--mg-ink);
    font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .mgp-head { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 36px; }
  .mgp-kicker {
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.26em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--mg-clay);
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }
  .mgp-title {
    font-family: var(--mg-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 40px;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--mg-ink);
  }

  .mgp-block { margin-bottom: 36px; }
  .mgp-block h2 {
    font-family: var(--mg-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 24px;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    color: var(--mg-moss);
    border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--mg-rule);
    padding-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .mgp-bold {
    font-size: 19px;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .mgp-bold p { margin: 0 0 14px; color: var(--mg-ink); }
  .mgp-bold strong { font-weight: 600; color: var(--mg-clay); }
  .mgp-bold em { font-family: var(--mg-display); font-style: italic; color: var(--mg-moss); }

  .mgp-does-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: 18px;
  }
  .mgp-does-h {
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--mg-clay);
    margin: 0 0 6px;
  }
  .mgp-does-grid p:not(.mgp-does-h) {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--mg-ink-soft);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .mgp-honest h2 em {
    font-family: var(--mg-display);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--mg-clay);
  }
  .mgp-honest ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .mgp-honest li {
    padding: 10px 0 10px 16px;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--mg-rule);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--mg-ink-soft);
  }
  .mgp-honest li strong {
    color: var(--mg-ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .mgp-technical ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--mg-ink-soft);
  }
  .mgp-technical li {
    padding: 4px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--mg-rule-soft);
  }
  .mgp-technical li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .mgp-technical li::before {
    content: '·  ';
    color: var(--mg-clay);
  }

  .mgp-who p {
    font-family: var(--mg-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--mg-ink-soft);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .mgp-who em {
    color: var(--mg-moss);
  }

  .mgp-cta {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 24px 0 12px;
    border-top: 1px dotted var(--mg-rule);
    margin-top: 48px;
  }
  .mgp-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    padding: 14px 28px;
    background: var(--mg-moss);
    color: var(--mg-paper);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .mgp-btn:hover { background: #273A28; }
  .mgp-cta-meta {
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--mg-ink-mute);
    margin: 10px 0 20px;
  }
  .mgp-nav {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 20px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .mgp-nav a {
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--mg-bronze);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .mgp-nav a:hover { color: var(--mg-clay); }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .mgp-title { font-size: 28px; }
    .mgp-bold { font-size: 17px; }
  }
</style>
